al district of Epping|Epping]] || 2007\u20132015\n|-\n|| Hon [[George Souris]] || National || [[Electoral district of Upper Hunter|Upper Hunter]] || 1988\u20132015\n|-\n|| [[Tony Stewart (Australian politician)|Tony Stewart]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Bankstown|Bankstown]] || 1995\u20132011\n|-\n|| [[Rob Stokes]] || Liberal || [[Electoral district of Pittwater|Pittwater]] || 2007\u2013present\n|-\n|| [[Andrew Stoner]] || National || [[Electoral district of Oxley (New South Wales)|Oxley]] || 1999\u20132015\n|-\n|| Hon [[Carmel Tebbutt]]  || Labor || [[Electoral district of Marrickville|Marrickville]] || 2005\u20132015\n|-\n|| [[Frank Terenzini]]  || Labor || [[Electoral district of Maitland|Maitland]] || 2007\u20132011\n|-\n|| [[Richard Torbay]] || Independent || [[Electoral district of Northern Tablelands|Northern Tablelands]] || 1999\u20132013\n|-\n|| [[Joe Tripodi]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Fairfield|Fairfield]] || 1995\u20132011\n|-\n|| [[John Turner (Australian politician)|John Turner]] || National || [[Electoral district of Myall Lakes|Myall Lakes]] || 1988\u20132011\n|-\n|| [[Russell Turner]] || National || [[Electoral district of Orange|Orange]] || 1996\u20132011\n|-\n|| Hon [[John Watkins (Australian politician)|John Watkins]] {{ref label|2|2|2}} || Labor || [[Electoral district of Ryde|Ryde]] || 1995\u20132008\n|-\n||Hon [[Graham West]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Campbelltown|Campbelltown]] || 2001\u20132011\n|-\n|| [[Steve Whan]] || Labor || [[Electoral district of Monaro|Monaro]] || 2003\u20132011\n|-\n|| [[John Williams (New South Wales state politician)|John Williams]] || National || [[Electoral district of Murray-Darling|Murray-Darling]] || 2007\u20132015\n|-\n|| [[Ray Williams (politician)|Ray Williams]] || Liberal || [[Electoral district of Hawkesbury|Hawkesbury]] || 2007\u2013present\n|}\n\n:{{note label|1|1|1}} Port Macquarie independent MLA [[Rob Oakeshott]] resigned on 13 August 2008 in order to contest a [[2008 Lyne by-election|federal by-election]] for the seat of [[Division of Lyne|Lyne]]. Independent candidate [[Peter Besseling]] won the [[2008 Port Macquarie state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 18 October.\n:{{note label|2|2|2}} Ryde Labor MLA and outgoing Deputy Premier [[John Watkins (Australian politician)|John Watkins]] resigned on 12 September 2008. Liberal candidate [[Victor Dominello]] won the [[2008 Ryde state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 18 October.\n:{{note label|3|3|3}} Cabramatta Labor MLA [[Reba Meagher]] resigned on 16 September 2008. Labor candidate [[Nick Lalich]] won the [[2008 Cabramatta state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 18 October.\n:{{note label|4|4|4}} Lakemba Labor MLA and outgoing Premier [[Morris Iemma]] resigned on 19 September 2008. Labor candidate [[Robert Furolo]] won the [[2008 Lakemba state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 18 October.\n:{{note label|5|5|5}} Penrith MLA [[Karyn Paluzzano]] was suspended from the Labor Party on 6 May 2010 after being found to have lied to the [[Independent Commission Against Corruption (New South Wales)|Independent Commission Against Corruption]]. She subsequently resigned from parliament on 7 May. Liberal candidate [[Stuart Ayres]] won the [[2010 Penrith state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 19 June.\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[2007 New South Wales state election]]\n* Premiers:\n** [[Morris Iemma]] ([[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]) (2005\u20132008)\n** [[Nathan Rees]] ([[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]) (2008\u20132009)\n** [[Kristina Keneally]] ([[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]) (2009\u20132011)\n\n{{Members of the Parliament of New South Wales}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Members Of The New South Wales Legislative Assembly, 2007-2011}}\n[[Category:Members of New South Wales parliaments by term]]\n[[Category:20th-century Australian politicians]]\n", "