nt candidate [[Peter Besseling]] won the [[2008 Port Macquarie state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 18 October.\n:{{note label|2|2|2}} Ryde Labor MLA and outgoing Deputy Premier [[John Watkins (Australian politician)|John Watkins]] resigned on 12 September 2008. Liberal candidate [[Victor Dominello]] won the [[2008 Ryde state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 18 October.\n:{{note label|3|3|3}} Cabramatta Labor MLA [[Reba Meagher]] resigned on 16 September 2008. Labor candidate [[Nick Lalich]] won the [[2008 Cabramatta state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 18 October.\n:{{note label|4|4|4}} Lakemba Labor MLA and outgoing Premier [[Morris Iemma]] resigned on 19 September 2008. Labor candidate [[Robert Furolo]] won the [[2008 Lakemba state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 18 October.\n:{{note label|5|5|5}} Penrith MLA [[Karyn Paluzzano]] was suspended from the Labor Party on 6 May 2010 after being found to have lied to the [[Independent Commission Against Corruption (New South Wales)|Independent Commission Against Corruption]]. She subsequently resigned from parliament on 7 May. Liberal candidate [[Stuart Ayres]] won the [[2010 Penrith state by-election|resulting by-election]] on 19 June.\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[2007 New South Wales state election]]\n* Premiers:\n** [[Morris Iemma]] ([[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]) (2005\u20132008)\n** [[Nathan Rees]] ([[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]) (2008\u20132009)\n** [[Kristina Keneally]] ([[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]) (2009\u20132011)\n\n{{Members of the Parliament of New South Wales}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Members Of The New South Wales Legislative Assembly, 2007-2011}}\n[[Category:Members of New South Wales parliaments by term]]\n[[Category:20th-century Australian politicians]]\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSee also:Update date format tag and 